title: Bulk Enroll Members -Batch Size
body:
GUS - https://gus.lightning.force.com/lightning/r/ADM_Work__c/a07EE00001GkyqBYAR/view
Issue: The batchSize provided in the options map/remote options always create one batch per job.
Reason: Every record in the input list of (primary and dependents), passed to the vlocity framework , is equivalent to a batch (of given batch size) which means every input list records should be treated as a batch of size 1 in the vlocityFramework for asynchronous. Also, the batch size is only read from option map in the vlocityFramework and if it is not provided, it will be considered of batch size is 1.
Fix: The options map is updated to set BatchSize to 1 while submitting input list to the vlocityFramework.

title: Fixed Timezone issue of one day differnce in modify policy modal for orgs ahead of UTC timezone.
body:
Bug Reference - https://gus.lightning.force.com/lightning/r/ADM_Work__c/a07EE000016py6eYAA/view
### The issue 
When click the modify policy modal on the insurance policy the effective date and end date shown in the modal was one day prior to policy effective date and end date.(In the org's with timezone ahead of UTC like if org's timezone is set to IST).
### Root cause
When the values of fields are fetched from DB the effective date and end date are datetime fields in policy and the DB return these fields in the UTC Timezone. So for the org's whose timezone is ahead of UTC this would one day prior.
Example : in IST (2022-12-1T00:00:00Z) would be (2022-11-30T18:30:00Z) in UTC. So the effective date and end date fields in modal were showing one day before.
### Fix
The fix for this is to convert the datetime value from DB to local timezone and extract the date from it.
When issuing quote added a check if any value is datetime convert it to UTC .
